<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4cfdb52b-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12212"><num value="12212">§ 12212.</num><heading> Prohibition</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">None of the funds authorized under this part shall be used to finance the construction of housing.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4cfdb52c-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tIII/s31133">Pub. L. 103–322, title III, § 31133</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1888">108 Stat. 1888</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4cfdb52d-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id4cfdb52e-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id4cfdb52f-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s13853">section 13853 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
